 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Markowitz Mean-Variance Portfolio Optimization with CVXPY\n",
    "\n",
    "> **Author:DHRUV PATEL | **Date:  February 2026  \n",
    "> **Purpose:** GSoC 2026 Pre-Application Portfolio \u2014 NumFOCUS / CVXPY Sub-Org\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## What This Notebook Covers\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook demonstrates how **CVXPY** \u2014 an open-source Python library for convex optimization \u2014 is used to solve real quantitative finance problems.\n",
    "\n",
    "We implement the classic **Markowitz Mean-Variance model** (1952) from scratch, covering:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Downloading real stock return data with `yfinance`\n",
    "2. Estimating expected returns and the covariance matrix\n",
    "3. Formulating the portfolio optimization problem as a **Quadratic Program (QP)** in CVXPY\n",
    "4. Solving for the **Minimum Variance Portfolio**\n",
    "5. Solving for the **Maximum Sharpe Ratio Portfolio**\n",
    "6. Tracing the full **Efficient Frontier**\n",
    "7. Adding **real-world constraints**: long-only, weight limits, sector caps\n",
    "8. Visualizing results\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Why CVXPY for Portfolio Optimization?\n",
    "\n",
    "Portfolio optimization is fundamentally a **convex optimization problem**. CVXPY lets us express it exactly as the math states \u2014 no reformulation needed. The same workflow used here is employed at quantitative hedge funds, asset managers, and trading desks globally.\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "minimize    w^T \u03a3 w              (portfolio variance)\n",
    "subject to  w^T \u03bc >= r_target   (minimum return)\n",
    "            sum(w) = 1          (fully invested)\n",
    "            w >= 0              (long only)\n",
    "```"
   ],
   "id": "cell-intro"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Install and Import Libraries"
   ],
   "id": "cell-md-imports"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Install required packages (run once)\n",
    "# !pip install cvxpy yfinance numpy pandas matplotlib seaborn scipy\n",
    "\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import matplotlib.ticker as mtick\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "import cvxpy as cp\n",
    "import yfinance as yf\n",
    "import warnings\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plotting style\n",
    "plt.rcParams['figure.figsize'] = (12, 6)\n",
    "plt.rcParams['font.family'] = 'DejaVu Sans'\n",
    "sns.set_style('whitegrid')\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'CVXPY version: {cp.__version__}')\n",
    "print('All libraries loaded successfully.')"
   ],
   "id": "cell-imports"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Download Real Stock Data\n\nWe use 10 large-cap US equities across different sectors for a realistic portfolio universe."
   ],
   "id": "cell-md-data"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# \u2500\u2500 Portfolio Universe \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\n",
    "TICKERS = {\n",
    "    'AAPL':  'Technology',\n",
    "    'MSFT':  'Technology',\n",
    "    'GOOGL': 'Technology',\n",
    "    'JPM':   'Financials',\n",
    "    'GS':    'Financials',\n",
    "    'JNJ':   'Healthcare',\n",
    "    'PFE':   'Healthcare',\n",
    "    'XOM':   'Energy',\n",
    "    'CVX':   'Energy',\n",
    "    'SPY':   'Benchmark',\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "ASSETS = [t for t in TICKERS if t != 'SPY']  # exclude benchmark from portfolio\n",
    "ALL    = list(TICKERS.keys())\n",
    "\n",
    "# Download 3 years of daily closing prices\n",
    "print('Downloading price data from Yahoo Finance...')\n",
    "raw = yf.download(ALL, start='2021-01-01', end='2024-01-01',\n",
    "                  auto_adjust=True, progress=False)['Close']\n",
    "\n",
    "raw.dropna(inplace=True)\n",
    "print(f'Downloaded {len(raw)} trading days for {len(ALL)} tickers.')\n",
    "raw.tail(3)"
   ],
   "id": "cell-download"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# \u2500\u2500 Compute Daily Log Returns \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\n",
    "returns = np.log(raw / raw.shift(1)).dropna()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Separate portfolio assets from benchmark\n",
    "port_returns = returns[ASSETS]\n",
    "spy_returns  = returns['SPY']\n",
    "\n",
    "# \u2500\u2500 Annualised Statistics \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\n",
    "TRADING_DAYS = 252\n",
    "\n",
    "mu    = port_returns.mean() * TRADING_DAYS          # annualised expected returns (vector)\n",
    "Sigma = port_returns.cov()  * TRADING_DAYS          # annualised covariance matrix\n",
    "n     = len(ASSETS)                                 # number of assets\n",
    "\n",
    "print('\\nAnnualised Expected Returns:')\n",
    "print(mu.round(4).to_string())\n",
    "print(f'\\nCovariance Matrix Shape: {Sigma.shape}')\n",
    "print(f'Number of Assets: {n}')"
   ],
   "id": "cell-returns"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# \u2500\u2500 Visualise Correlation Matrix \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\n",
    "corr = port_returns.corr()\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(9, 7))\n",
    "sns.heatmap(corr, annot=True, fmt='.2f', cmap='RdYlGn',\n",
    "            center=0, vmin=-1, vmax=1, ax=ax,\n",
    "            linewidths=0.5, cbar_kws={'label': 'Pearson Correlation'})\n",
    "ax.set_title('Asset Correlation Matrix (2021-2024)', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold', pad=15)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('correlation_matrix.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "print('Key insight: Low/negative correlations = better diversification benefits.')"
   ],
   "id": "cell-corr"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Core CVXPY Problem Formulation\n\n",
    "This is the heart of the notebook. We express the Markowitz QP directly in CVXPY.\n\n",
    "The beauty of CVXPY is that the code reads almost identically to the mathematical formulation:\n\n",
    "```\n",
    "minimize    (1/2) * w^T \u03a3 w\n",
    "subject to  1^T w = 1          (weights sum to 1)\n",
    "            w >= 0             (long-only constraint)\n",
    "```"
   ],
   "id": "cell-md-cvxpy"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# \u2500\u2500 Helper: Solve Portfolio Optimisation Problem \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\n",
    "def solve_portfolio(\n",
    "    mu: np.ndarray,\n",
    "    Sigma: np.ndarray,\n",
    "    target_return: float = None,\n",
    "    long_only: bool = True,\n",
    "    max_weight: float = 1.0,\n",
    "    sector_caps: dict = None,\n",
    "    risk_aversion: float = None,\n",
    ") -> dict:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Solve the Markowitz Mean-Variance portfolio optimisation using CVXPY.\n",
    "\n",
    "    Parameters\n",
    "    ----------\n",
    "    mu            : (n,) expected returns vector (annualised)\n",
    "    Sigma         : (n, n) covariance matrix (annualised)\n",
    "    target_return : if given, adds minimum return constraint\n",
    "    long_only     : if True, w >= 0\n",
    "    max_weight    : maximum allocation per asset (default 1.0 = no cap)\n",
    "    sector_caps   : dict {sector_name: (indices, max_allocation)}\n",
    "    risk_aversion : if given, solves mean-variance utility instead\n",
    "\n",
    "    Returns\n",
    "    -------\n",
    "    dict with weights, portfolio return, portfolio volatility, sharpe ratio\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    n = len(mu)\n",
    "    w = cp.Variable(n)  # portfolio weights \u2014 the decision variable\n",
    "\n",
    "    # \u2500\u2500 Objective \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\n",
    "    # Portfolio variance: w^T Sigma w  (quad_form is CVXPY's QP expression)\n",
    "    portfolio_variance = cp.quad_form(w, Sigma)\n",
    "\n",
    "    if risk_aversion is not None:\n",
    "        # Mean-variance utility: maximise \u03bc^T w - \u03bb/2 * w^T \u03a3 w\n",
    "        objective = cp.Minimize(portfolio_variance - (1 / risk_aversion) * (mu @ w))\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        # Pure minimum variance\n",
    "        objective = cp.Minimize(portfolio_variance)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # \u2500\u2500 Constraints \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\n",
    "    constraints = [\n",
    "        cp.sum(w) == 1,           # fully invested\n",
    "    ]\n",
    "\n",
    "    if long_only:\n",
    "        constraints.append(w >= 0)             # no short selling\n",
    "\n",
    "    if max_weight < 1.0:\n",
    "        constraints.append(w <= max_weight)    # single-asset cap\n",
    "\n",
    "    if target_return is not None:\n",
    "        constraints.append(mu @ w >= target_return)  # minimum return\n",
    "\n",
    "    if sector_caps:\n",
    "        for sector, (idx, cap) in sector_caps.items():\n",
    "            constraints.append(cp.sum(w[idx]) <= cap)  # sector exposure cap\n",
    "\n",
    "    # \u2500\u2500 Solve \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\n",
    "    problem = cp.Problem(objective, constraints)\n",
    "    problem.solve(solver=cp.SCS, verbose=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "    if problem.status not in ['optimal', 'optimal_inaccurate']:\n",
    "        return None  # infeasible (e.g. target return too high)\n",
    "\n",
    "    weights = np.array(w.value).flatten()\n",
    "    weights = np.clip(weights, 0, 1)  # clean up tiny numerical noise\n",
    "    weights /= weights.sum()           # renormalise\n",
    "\n",
    "    port_ret = float(mu @ weights)\n",
    "    port_vol = float(np.sqrt(weights @ Sigma @ weights))\n",
    "    rf       = 0.05  # risk-free rate (5% approximate 2024)\n",
    "    sharpe   = (port_ret - rf) / port_vol\n",
    "\n",
    "    return {\n",
    "        'weights':    weights,\n",
    "        'return':     port_ret,\n",
    "        'volatility': port_vol,\n",
    "        'sharpe':     sharpe,\n",
    "        'status':     problem.status,\n",
    "    }\n",
    "\n",
    "print('solve_portfolio() function defined.')\n",
    "print('This wraps the CVXPY QP formulation into a clean, reusable interface.')"
   ],
   "id": "cell-solver"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Minimum Variance Portfolio"
   ],
   "id": "cell-md-minvar"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "mu_np    = mu.values\n",
    "Sigma_np = Sigma.values\n",
    "\n",
    "# \u2500\u2500 Solve: Minimum Variance Portfolio \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\n",
    "min_var = solve_portfolio(mu_np, Sigma_np, long_only=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "print('=' * 55)\n",
    "print('  MINIMUM VARIANCE PORTFOLIO (Long-Only)')\n",
    "print('=' * 55)\n",
    "print(f\"  Expected Return : {min_var['return']*100:.2f}% p.a.\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Volatility      : {min_var['volatility']*100:.2f}% p.a.\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Sharpe Ratio    : {min_var['sharpe']:.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Solver Status   : {min_var['status']}\")\n",
    "print()\n",
    "print('  Asset Weights:')\n",
    "for asset, w in sorted(zip(ASSETS, min_var['weights']), key=lambda x: -x[1]):\n",
    "    bar = '\u2588' * int(w * 40)\n",
    "    print(f\"  {asset:6s}  {w*100:6.2f}%  {bar}\")"
   ],
   "id": "cell-minvar"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Maximum Sharpe Ratio Portfolio\n\nWe trace the efficient frontier across target returns and find the portfolio maximising Sharpe ratio."
   ],
   "id": "cell-md-sharpe"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# \u2500\u2500 Trace the Efficient Frontier \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\n",
    "r_min    = float(mu_np.min()) + 0.01\n",
    "r_max    = float(mu_np.max()) - 0.01\n",
    "targets  = np.linspace(r_min, r_max, 60)\n",
    "\n",
    "frontier = []\n",
    "for r_target in targets:\n",
    "    result = solve_portfolio(mu_np, Sigma_np,\n",
    "                             target_return=r_target,\n",
    "                             long_only=True)\n",
    "    if result is not None:\n",
    "        frontier.append(result)\n",
    "\n",
    "front_returns = np.array([p['return']     for p in frontier])\n",
    "front_vols    = np.array([p['volatility'] for p in frontier])\n",
    "front_sharpes = np.array([p['sharpe']     for p in frontier])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Maximum Sharpe portfolio\n",
    "best_idx  = np.argmax(front_sharpes)\n",
    "max_sharpe = frontier[best_idx]\n",
    "\n",
    "print('=' * 55)\n",
    "print('  MAXIMUM SHARPE RATIO PORTFOLIO')\n",
    "print('=' * 55)\n",
    "print(f\"  Expected Return : {max_sharpe['return']*100:.2f}% p.a.\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Volatility      : {max_sharpe['volatility']*100:.2f}% p.a.\")\n",
    "print(f\"  Sharpe Ratio    : {max_sharpe['sharpe']:.4f}\")\n",
    "print()\n",
    "print('  Asset Weights:')\n",
    "for asset, w in sorted(zip(ASSETS, max_sharpe['weights']), key=lambda x: -x[1]):\n",
    "    bar = '\u2588' * int(w * 40)\n",
    "    print(f\"  {asset:6s}  {w*100:6.2f}%  {bar}\")"
   ],
   "id": "cell-sharpe"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Plot the Efficient Frontier"
   ],
   "id": "cell-md-plot"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# \u2500\u2500 Individual Asset Risk/Return Points \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\n",
    "asset_vols    = np.sqrt(np.diag(Sigma_np))\n",
    "asset_returns = mu_np\n",
    "\n",
    "# \u2500\u2500 Plot \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 7))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Efficient frontier line \u2014 coloured by Sharpe ratio\n",
    "sc = ax.scatter(front_vols * 100, front_returns * 100,\n",
    "                c=front_sharpes, cmap='RdYlGn',\n",
    "                s=18, zorder=3, label='Efficient Frontier')\n",
    "plt.colorbar(sc, ax=ax, label='Sharpe Ratio')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Individual assets\n",
    "for i, asset in enumerate(ASSETS):\n",
    "    ax.scatter(asset_vols[i]*100, asset_returns[i]*100,\n",
    "               marker='D', s=80, zorder=5, color='steelblue')\n",
    "    ax.annotate(asset,\n",
    "                (asset_vols[i]*100, asset_returns[i]*100),\n",
    "                textcoords='offset points', xytext=(6, 4),\n",
    "                fontsize=9, color='steelblue')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Minimum variance point\n",
    "ax.scatter(min_var['volatility']*100, min_var['return']*100,\n",
    "           marker='*', s=300, color='navy', zorder=6,\n",
    "           label=f\"Min Variance  (Sharpe={min_var['sharpe']:.2f})\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Maximum Sharpe point\n",
    "ax.scatter(max_sharpe['volatility']*100, max_sharpe['return']*100,\n",
    "           marker='*', s=300, color='darkgreen', zorder=6,\n",
    "           label=f\"Max Sharpe  (Sharpe={max_sharpe['sharpe']:.2f})\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Capital Market Line\n",
    "rf = 0.05\n",
    "slope = (max_sharpe['return'] - rf) / max_sharpe['volatility']\n",
    "cml_x = np.linspace(0, front_vols.max() * 1.1, 100)\n",
    "cml_y = rf + slope * cml_x\n",
    "ax.plot(cml_x * 100, cml_y * 100, 'k--', alpha=0.5, linewidth=1.2,\n",
    "        label='Capital Market Line')\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('Portfolio Volatility (Annualised %)', fontsize=12)\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('Portfolio Expected Return (Annualised %)', fontsize=12)\n",
    "ax.set_title('Markowitz Efficient Frontier (CVXPY)\\n9-Asset US Equity Portfolio 2021\u20132024',\n",
    "             fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "ax.legend(fontsize=10)\n",
    "ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(mtick.FormatStrFormatter('%.1f%%'))\n",
